  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe deposit contract does not verify BLS signatures or pubkeys and therefore they may contain arbitrary bytes.\r\n\r\nPresently we would fail to parse any `Deposit` with an invalid signature or pubkey, this is a consensus-breaking bug.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nMy suggestion is to create a `MaybeInvalidSignature` (or more aptly named) wrapper around `Signature` that permits parsing invalid bytes and implement it only for `Deposit`. That way we get to keep our parsing safety for other objects.\r\n\r\nEDIT: I updated this issue because it needs to cover `PublicKey` as well as `Signature`.\r\n",
